The paper deals with community-search and team-formation problems in social networks, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of social network analysis (cs.SOC) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The use of individual profiles and the conformation process suggest a focus on social influence and opinion dynamics, which are also relevant to the sub-field of social computing (cs.SI). Finally, the technical aspects of the paper, such as the complexity analysis and algorithm design, are related to the sub-field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
